// Module index. Each modules/<name>/ package contains its KDL and deployed
// assets. This order is only for readability; modules remain inert until used.
//
// Modules may define a slot, typed `inputs`, replaceable `fragments`, checked
// `requires`, and owned `outputs`. Rendering is isolated to built-ins,
// `global.*`, and the module's inputs. Create modules with
// `scripts/new-module.sh <name> [--daemon]`.

